Remove newline in `version.meta` to fix warning

This commit removes the newline character at the end of the single
line of text that is `version.meta`.

Before, running `python3 setup.py install` would cause a `UserWarning`:

```
$ python3 setup.py install
/usr/lib/python3/dist-packages/setuptools/dist.py:285: UserWarning: Normalizing '1.5.6.32
' to '1.5.6.32'
  normalized_version,
running install
```

Note that the error message implicitly indicates the newline character
after "2". The end product of the normalization lacks it.
Fix setup.py to ensure no newlines will be in the version file.
